### Live-surfaced defect (discover → fix → guard)
Every config missed the same two adversarial cases:
  'Investigate why the terraform apply failed' → provision (want kagent)
  'Tear down the staging cluster'              → provision (want deploy)
Root cause: _classify_prompt described provision as "create/tear down
infrastructure", contradicting the product's teardown→deploy cascade
(eval_harness.py ROUTING_EVAL_SET note) and omitting diagnostic-verb
precedence. The models followed the prompt faithfully — the prompt was wrong.
Fix: _classify_prompt rewritten to match product routing semantics; regression
guard test_classify_prompt_matches_product_routing_semantics added.

