  7B/low 0.80→1.00 · 7B/high 0.75→0.90 · 30B/low 0.80→0.95 · 30B/high 0.80→0.95

## Evidence-based pick
Qwen2.5-Coder-7B @ temperature 0 wins outright for routing classification:
100% on the 20-case set (adversarial included), fastest per success, and ~4×
smaller than the 30B — the static "bigger model for routing" annotation is not
supported by measurement. Temperature 0 beats 1.0 on both models for this
single-token-ish classification task.

Notes:
- Sweep resume verified live: run 2 per-model invocations merged into one
  points file via done= dedup (no re-spend on completed configs).
- served-model guard corrected during the run: mlx_lm.server /v1/models lists
  all cached models (availability), the request's `model` field selects per
  call; the script now verifies the response echoes the requested model and
  refuses to persist a backstop-contaminated run.
